/Type /StructElem
/S /H1
/P 162 0 R
/T (Continuity: When a human blacksmith leaves, AI blacksmiths continue production. The economy bends rather than breaks. Human absence creates inefficiency, not collapse. Demand: AI agents eat food, wear out tools, need housing, consume goods. They create perpetual demand that keeps the economy active after humans have everything they need. Tedium: Repetitive necessary labor can be performed by AI agents. Humans can focus on creative, strategic, or social activities while AI handles routine production. Political mass: Laws affect a real population. Governance has weight because there are constituents whose behavior responds to policy. Server health: The AI population provides resilience against the death spiral that kills traditional multiplayer servers. Temporal flexibility: Players can engage when they want without obligation to prevent server collapse. The world continues without them but clearly benefits from their presence.)
/E (Continuity: When a human blacksmith leaves, AI blacksmiths continue production. The economy bends rather than breaks. Human absence creates inefficiency, not collapse. Demand: AI agents eat food, wear out tools, need housing, consume goods. They create perpetual demand that keeps the economy active after humans have everything they need. Tedium: Repetitive necessary labor can be performed by AI agents. Humans can focus on creative, strategic, or social activities while AI handles routine production. Political mass: Laws affect a real population. Governance has weight because there are constituents whose behavior responds to policy. Server health: The AI population provides resilience against the death spiral that kills traditional multiplayer servers. Temporal flexibility: Players can engage when they want without obligation to prevent server collapse. The world continues without them but clearly benefits from their presence.)
/Pg 20 0 R
/K [1]
>>
endobj
